<percentage>0</percentage></teachingTypeInCurriculum></teachingTypesInCurriculumYear></programCurriculum><programDescriptions><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The programme focuses on relevant and innovative practices around themes and issues which dominate the international discourse in social work and social policy. The programme provides an excellent opportunity for students who may be interested in studying abroad and would like to explore the possibility within the frame of a short program.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>objectives</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Focuses on relevant and innovative practices around themes and issues which dominate the international discourse in social work and social policy.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>curriculum</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><contentLink><contentSummary xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Lectures, workgroup or workshops and a synthesis. Guest lecturers or international speakers are integrated in the morning programme. This will be supplemented in the afternoon either with a training related to the morning topic, a field visit or time to work on the assignment.]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>instruction modes</subject><webLink xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[The Amsterdam School of Social Work and Law (SSWL) is pleased to present its first summer course: Groups at Risk: Citizenship & Civic Participation. In this summer course, international students will be confronted with challenging topics presented by and discussed with top teachers, international speakers, innovative projects, major institutions and Dutch students. 

Amsterdam, a cosmopolitan city in the delta of Europe, is a laboratory where history and the future meet one another. This makes Amsterdam the perfect testing ground to study and to explore the role of social work and social policy in urban areas.

